Related Work
1. Multimodal Instruction-Following Agents
A. End-to-End Trained Models
A single model directly learns the entire task.
Designed for specific applications.
Examples:
Vision-Language Navigation
Habitat
InstructPix2Pix (image editing using text instructions)

Limitation: Usually task-specific and less flexible for general-purpose interaction.

B. Multi-Model Systems with LLMs
Combine multiple specialized models through an LLM.
Examples:
Visual ChatGPT
X-GPT
MM-REACT
VisProg
ViperGPT

Limitation: Depend on multiple external modules instead of a unified model.

LLaVA's Approach
Builds a single end-to-end multimodal model.
Directly connects vision understanding with language generation.
Designed to handle multiple vision-language tasks through one interface

2. Instruction Tuning
What is Instruction Tuning?
Training a model on instruction-answer pairs.
Helps the model follow natural language commands.
Improves:
Zero-shot learning
Few-shot learning
Generalization to unseen tasks
